1
00:00:05,312 --> 00:00:06,924
As parents often do:

2
00:00:06,924 --> 00:00:10,101
they want their son to be this way, 
their daughter to be that way.

3
00:00:10,241 --> 00:00:13,736
[A Husband and a Paramour | 
Karmic Show]

4
00:00:13,911 --> 00:00:18,040
Hridayananda Mahārāj made a joke 
once, where he said that

5
00:00:18,830 --> 00:00:22,590
like in his case and 
Pusta Kṛṣṇa Prabhu’s,

6
00:00:22,590 --> 00:00:26,170
some others, who had 
a lot of high grades in college,

7
00:00:26,170 --> 00:00:29,026
“Their parents expected them 
to be doctors and lawyers,

8
00:00:29,026 --> 00:00:31,702
and they became devotees.”

9
00:00:31,702 --> 00:00:34,409
He said, “Now we have 
these devotees parents,

10
00:00:34,409 --> 00:00:36,231
and they have 
these children,

11
00:00:36,231 --> 00:00:39,479
and they want the kid 
to be a devotee,

12
00:00:39,479 --> 00:00:44,697
and he becomes a doctor
or a lawyer.” [Laughs]

13
00:00:46,077 --> 00:00:56,493
So, Hiranyakashipu—Prahlad. 
Then Bali—and the others.

14
00:00:56,493 --> 00:01:01,912
This is just as Congreve said, 
“The way of the world.”

15
00:01:01,912 --> 00:01:06,212
Still, Guru Mahārāj makes 
a very interesting observation,

16
00:01:11,487 --> 00:01:16,796
how, taking something 
like parakiya-bhav

17
00:01:16,796 --> 00:01:21,876
and pragmatically, 
practically applying it

18
00:01:21,876 --> 00:01:26,086
in the circumstances 
we find ourselves in.

19
00:01:26,256 --> 00:01:32,896
Saying that in Vedic system …

20
00:01:34,995 --> 00:01:39,515
(We shall all now employ 
the temporary suspension of disbelief).

21
00:01:39,515 --> 00:01:42,407
In Vedic culture

22
00:01:44,357 --> 00:01:50,279
the wife shall answer 
to the demands of the husband.

23
00:01:50,979 --> 00:01:53,752
This is the system.

24
00:01:56,440 --> 00:02:03,022
But in the case of a wife 
with a paramour,

25
00:02:03,022 --> 00:02:07,663
she still, she’s going to be attentive 
to the demands of the husband,

26
00:02:07,663 --> 00:02:11,274
but it’s more going to be a show.

27
00:02:11,274 --> 00:02:16,476
Whereas really in her heart 
she’s given over to the paramour.

28
00:02:17,708 --> 00:02:20,287
That’s the example.

29
00:02:20,287 --> 00:02:24,737
And what Guru Mahārāj 
is comparing this to, is saying,

30
00:02:25,371 --> 00:02:28,993
the baddha-jiva, 
the conditioned soul,

31
00:02:28,993 --> 00:02:32,519
tamasā bahu rūpeṇa 
veṣṭitāḥ karmahetunā—
[Manu: 1.49]

32
00:02:32,519 --> 00:02:37,208
in karmic dress, surrounded 
by karmic circumstances

33
00:02:37,208 --> 00:02:41,417
you’re like the wife, 
all of us, in this situation,

34
00:02:41,417 --> 00:02:46,418
and karma is like the husband,
saying,

35
00:02:46,430 --> 00:02:49,257
“So much exploitation 
you’ve done,

36
00:02:49,257 --> 00:02:52,594
you owe me something, 
I’ve come to collect that.

37
00:02:52,594 --> 00:02:57,123
You must now
fulfill my demands.”

38
00:02:58,327 --> 00:03:02,574
Guru Mahārāj is saying, 
“A devotee makes a show

39
00:03:02,574 --> 00:03:06,821
of fulfilling their 
karmic responsibilities,

40
00:03:06,821 --> 00:03:11,069
to family, friends, 
society, etc.

41
00:03:11,112 --> 00:03:18,152
While in their hearts, the heart 
is given over to Kṛṣṇa conception.”

